data.enText: a confused situation in which there is usually a lot of noise and excitement, often involving large numbers of people
a state in which your thoughts or feelings are confused

tr: the act of making a noisy disturbance
a state of commotion and noise and confusion

value.def: A tumult is a state of great confusion or excitement.

example.ex: A tumult of feelings inside her fought for supremacy.
...the recent tumult in global financial markets.
example.tran: 最近全球金融市场的混乱

gramarinfo.label: also no det, oft N <l>of</l> n

value.def: A tumult is a lot of noise made by a crowd of people.

example.ex: Round one ends, to a tumult of whistles, screams and shouts.
example.tran: 第一局比赛结束了，口哨声、尖叫声与呼喊声一片喧哗。

gramarinfo.label: also no det, oft N <l>of</l> n
